@maestromusica As long as there's an easy way to identify you in the FCC videos I don't think you need to worry about doubling them on your own channel because you can just link to the FCC videos.

If you're still insistent on having them on your own channel, what I'd suggest doing is editing the video to put a disclaimer at the start saying something like "This video was produced as a volunteer project for FreeCodeCamp. Please consider watching this video on their channel." and include the link in both the annotation and video description. I'd also ensure that the title/description/tags of the video are fairly minimal (e.g. in your videos, don't mention FCC, hikes, and any FCC-unique terms) since you'll want to have the FCC version found over yours when people are searching. 

Or you can just make them all private and include a link to a playlist of private videos (not sure if you can do this, but you can figure that out for yourself).

